Philippines Stocks: Aboitiz, Alliance, DMCI, Energy, Philex

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-08-16T04:34:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/philippines-stocks-aboitiz-alliance-dmci-energy-philex.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose for a fifth
straight day, gaining 0.9 percent to 4,372.70.  Aboitiz Transport System Corp. (ATS)  , the nation’s
largest shipping line, surged 40 percent to 1.84 pesos, the
sharpest gain since May 2004. The company said it posted second-
quarter profit of 153.6 million pesos ($3.63 million), compared
with a loss of 10.5 million pesos a year earlier.  Alliance Global Group Inc. (AGI)  , owner of the largest
Philippine casino, rose 2.3 percent to 11.42 pesos, the highest
close since Aug. 4. The company said first-half net income more
than doubled to 8.06 billion pesos from a year earlier.  DMCI Holdings Inc. (DMC)  , the largest Philippine
construction company, increased 3.5 percent to 42.65 pesos, the
steepest gain since July 14. Second-quarter profit increased to
a record 3.01 billion pesos from 2.77 billion pesos a year
earlier, a stock-exchange filing showed.  Energy Development Corp. (EDC)  , the nation’s largest
geothermal company, sank 3.4 percent to 6 pesos, the lowest
close since March 30. The company said it swung to a 2.3
billion-peso first-half loss from a 5.63 billion peso profit a
year earlier.  IP Converge Data Center Inc. (CLOUD)  , a provider of
managed data services and business solutions, advanced 5 percent
to 2.52 pesos, the sharpest gain since June 17. The company said
first-half net income increased 60 percent from a year earlier
to 33.5 million pesos.  IPVG Corp. (IP)  , a media content producer, climbed 3.1
percent to 1.32 pesos, the highest close since Aug. 5. The media
content producer said first-half net income increased to 296.7
million pesos ($7 million) from 10.18 million pesos a year
earlier.  Megaworld Corp. (MEG)  , a builder of residential and
office towers, climbed 3.7 percent to 1.99 pesos, the first gain
in three days. The developer posted second-quarter profit of
3.91 billion pesos, compared with 1.12 billion pesos a year ago,
a stock-exchange filing showed.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s biggest metals
producer, increased 3.6 percent to 28.60 pesos, the highest
close based on prices going back to January 1990, after the
company extended the life of its Padcal copper and gold mine to
2020 from 2017. The life of the mine may be extended beyond
2020, depending on economic conditions, Philex said in a
statement to the stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
